In [19]:
function haircolor(sex)
    bar(
        freq2[:,sex],
        bar_width = 1,
        xlabel = "Hair color",
        xticks = (1:4, names(freq)[1]), # 
        ylabel = "Number of students",
        title = "Distribution of hair color in $(lowercase(sex)) students.",
    )
end

plots = Array{Any, 1}(undef, 4)
for (j, eye) in enumerate([:Blue, :Brown, :Green, :Hazel])
    plots[j] = groupedbar(
        freq3[:, j, :],
        bar_position = :dodge,
        xlabel = "Hair color",
        xticks = (1:4, names(freq3)[1]),
        titlefont = (10, "times"),
        title = "Eye:$eye",
        )
end
